title: Honduras Inflation Rate MoM
description: The Consumer Price Index in Honduras increased 0.66 percent in October of 2022 over the previous month. Inflation Rate MoM in Honduras averaged 0.72 percent from 1992 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 5.15 percent in February of 1995 and a record low of -0.65 percent in May of 2020. Inflation Rate MoM measures month over month change in the price of goods and services. This page provides - Honduras Inflation Rate MoM- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Banco Central de Honduras
